<F P=100> Colombia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Army Continues Search </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Army Continues Search </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0204022594 Santa Fe de Bogota Emisoras Caracol Network in 
Spanish 0102 GMT 2 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0204022594 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Emisoras Caracol Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Ever Rincon] </F>
  [Text] The Army is continuing its intensive search 
operations in an attempt to rescue U.S. citizen Ramon Rissen 
safe and sound. Rissen is the security chief at the Summer 
Linguistic Institute in Loma Linda, Meta Department. General 
Luis Bernardo Urbina Sanchez, commander of the Army's 7th 
Brigade, has commented on this kidnapping and other issues for 
Radio Caracol. 
  [Begin Urbina recording] He was riding a motorcycle along 
the 
highway between the municipal capital of Puerto Lleras and Loma 
Linda, where the Summer Linguistic Institute operates. During 
the trip he was intercepted by individuals we believe are--or we 
are certain are--members of the 43d Front of the FARC 
[Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia]. They violently took 
him away. We had certain information about where they initially 
took him, but we learned later they had moved. We have been 
unable to recontact them. [end recording] 
  Urbina also said there is no information on the whereabouts 
of the two U.S. missionaries Steve Welch and Timothy Vandyck, 
whom FARC guerrillas also kidnapped in the hamlet of San Jose, 
near Villavicencio, on 16 January. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

