<F P=100> Colombia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Presidential Guard Commandant Removed From Post </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Presidential Guard Commandant Removed From Post </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0304043794 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 in Spanish 1800 GMT 2 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0304043794 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 </F>

<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "NTC News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The investigation into the suicide of Private 
Leonardo Castro has led to the removal of Colonel Carlos Pinzon, 
commandant of the Presidential Guard Battalion. 
  [Begin General Norberto Adrada, Army 13th Brigade commander, 
recording] We have decided to relieve the colonel to allow a 
smoother investigation, without any kind of obstacle. 
Lieutenant Lozano was also moved, primarily to make the 
investigation process a little easier. [end recording] 
  For the same reasons, Pinzon was not present for today's 
change of command ceremonies. His future in the army is being 
questioned. 
  [Begin Adrada recording] That is a decision the commander of 
the Army must make. It is something we are evaluating, as you 
know, because the investigations are continuing. The Army 
commander will make the final decision. [end recording] 
  Regarding Ricardo Lozano, the 13th Brigade commander simply 
said he had been transferred to a position similar to the one he 
held when the tragic events occurred. The new commander of the 
Presidential Guard is Colonel Jose Domingo Rubio, former 
commander of the Military School. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

