<F P=106> [Report by Donald Gonzalez] </F>
  [Text] The Constitutionality Court issued a statement 
today. The document states, as you all know, that 
Constitutionality Court President Epaminondas Gonzalez Dubon was 
murdered yesterday and that the following points must be duly 
considered: 
  The first point strongly condemns the murder of 
Constitutionality Court President Epaminandas Gonzalez Dubon. 
The second point is very important. The Constitutional Court 
warns authorities to refrain from labeling the crime a priority 
before concluding the investigations because this [words 
indistinct] the magnitude of the crime but also mars the 
victim's outstanding honor. Third, it expresses its sincere 
condolences to Gonzalez' relatives, and fourth it will send a 
copy of this statement to the constitutional courts of friendly 
countries. 
  The Constitutionality Court issued this statement today on 
the murder of its president, Magistrate Epaminondas Gonzalez 
Dubon. It is signed by acting President (Daniel Larios 
Cifuentes) and Magistrates Edmundo Vasquez Martinez, Jose 
Antonio Monzono Juarez, Manuel Arturo Garcia, Carlos Enrique 
Reinoso Sill, and (Abel Gonzalez Rivas). 

