<F P=100> Guatemala </F>
<H3> <TI>   U.S. Citizen Sustains Irreversible Brain Damage </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    U.S. Citizen Sustains Irreversible Brain Damage </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0204025194 Guatemala City Cadena de Emisoras Unidas in 
Spanish 0137 GMT 2 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0204025194 </F>
<F P=104>  Guatemala City Cadena de Emisoras Unidas </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Diego Andres de Gatica] </F>
  [Text] U.S. citizen (June Diane Tomarweeks), 54, has 
irreversible brain damage. She is in the intensive care ward of 
Herrera Llerandi Hospital, Guatemala City. The medical report 
states her condition has stabilized, but she will have to remain 
in intensive care. Physicians have reported they had planned to 
send her to the United States, but the trip will have to wait at 
least four or five days. 
  A mob that confused her with a child kidnapper attacked the 
U.S. citizen in San Cristobal Alta Verapaz. The hospital 
information indicates her condition has stabilized but that the 
damage to her brain is irreversible. 

</TEXT>

