<F P=100> Guatemala </F>
<H3> <TI>   Gunmen Kill Constitutionality Court President </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Gunmen Kill Constitutionality Court President </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0204151894 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 1454 GMT 2 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA0204151894 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City NOTIMEX </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Guatemala City, 2 Apr (NOTIMEX) -- Constitutionality 
Court President Epaminondas Gonzalez was killed this morning by 
a group of unidentified gunmen who shot him as he entered his 
home, a local radio station reported today. 
  Sources close to the Gonzalez family said the magistrate was 
attacked this morning in the downtown Zona Dos neighborhood of 
the capital a few blocks from the National Palace as he entered 
his home. He died early this morning. Gonzalez sustained a 
fatal gunshot wound to the left side of his chest, according to 
Radio Sonora. 
  Last week the Constitutionality Court had declared the 
electoral law reforms being debated by the congressional 
deputies unconstitutional because "the reforms totally change 
the law." The reforms were agreed upon by the deputies and 
President Ramiro de Leon Carpio as part of a package of reforms 
to the Constitution which was approved in the January referendum. 

</TEXT>

