<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   ANPP Schedules Special Finance Session for 1 May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    ANPP Schedules Special Finance Session for 1 May </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0104132894 Havana PRENSA LATINA in Spanish 0939 GMT 1 Apr 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> PA0104132894 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana PRENSA LATINA </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Havana, 1 Apr (PL) -- The National Assembly of the 
People's Government [ANPP] (parliament) of Cuba will hold an 
extraordinary session on 1 May, according to a summons by the 
Council of State divulged today in this capital. 
  The newspaper GRANMA published the document on its front 
page 
today which notes that the objective of the meeting will be to 
analyze the country's internal financial situation. 
  The holding of the important Cuban parliament meeting was 
suggested by President Fidel Castro, on delivering the closing 
speech at the plenum of the national committee of the Cuban 
Workers Federation, which began early this week. 
  The workers plenum -- known here as the workers parliament 
-- 
reviewed a vast analysis process in work centers on the island, 
the purpose of which was to have the participants propose 
possible solutions to the current primary national economic 
problems. 
  The suggestions of over 3 million workers participating in 
the meetings, as the Cuban president has said, will be 
considered in the upcoming sessions of deputies, who will adopt 
a series of economic measures aimed at improving the country's 
internal financial situation and boosting its economic 
efficiency. 

</TEXT>

