<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Considers Establishing Dealership </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL0404224894 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1700 
GMT 4 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0404224894 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] (Martin Roddin), representative of the Japanese 
Mitsubishi Automobile Corporation, has said in Havana that 
Mitsubishi is studying the possibility of establishing a 
dealership office in Cuba to sell vehicles and spare parts, in 
addition to offering maintenance services. 
  According to (Roddin), the Japanese company intends to sell 
a 
line of vehicles for tourism and rental service, as well as 
trucks for the sugar industry. (Roddin) ruled out an immediate 
decision on this project, however, because these are medium- and 
long-term prospects. 
  Today, a Japanese company delegation began a series of 
consultations with Cuban economic circles to evaluate the 
project. Mitsubishi is the tenth-largest automobile industry in 
the world, manufacturing a total of 2 million units annually. 

</TEXT>

