<F P=100> Other Countries </F>
<H3> <TI>   Conference Denounces International Community </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Conference Denounces International Community </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL0404224794 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole in French 1600 
GMT 4 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0404224794 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Committee for Research and Communication of the 
Haitian Religious Conference, CHR, published an Easter 
reflection in which it criticizes the attitude of the 
international community toward the Haitian crisis. The increase 
in crime and repression in Haiti coincides with the so-called 
parliamentary plan supported by the U.S. Administration, writes 
CHR. 
  After reading recent news releases by the UN/OAS civilian 
mission on increased violence in Haiti, the Haitian Religious 
Conference asserts that hands washed in vain by U.S. 
Administration authorities, and all those who together with them 
plan for the death of innocent people, are stained by their 
victims' blood. The Haitian Religious Conference especially 
denounces the contradictions and disparities between the 
international community's words and deeds in Haiti's case. 

</TEXT>

