<F P=100> Other Countries </F>
<H3> <TI>   Parties Await Legislative Response to `Ultimatum' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Parties Await Legislative Response to `Ultimatum' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL0404213994 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole in French 1145 
GMT 4 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0404213994 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The week began with a new initiative by the 
political parties to unblock the crisis situation, notably an 
ultimatum that is scheduled to expire at the beginning of this 
week. 
  Last week, Front for Haitian Advancement and Progress; 
Hubert 
de Ronceray's Mobilization For National Development; the 
National Conference; and the Congress of Haitian People for 
National Rescue submitted a joint resolution demanding a 
solution to the political crisis. The leaders of these political 
parties suggested the definitive closing of the file on 
negotiating the return of President Aristide, the restoration of 
state authority, the priority of a national constitutional 
solution, the formation of an ad hoc government capable of 
managing the embargo and executing a precise political agenda, 
and finally, the organization of general elections. 
  The promoters of this resolution assert they have received a 
very large consensus on this proposal, a copy of which was sent 
to the Army General Staff, the Chamber of Deputies, as well as 
organizations and institutions from civilian society. In this 
resolution, an ultimatum was given to parliament. Parliament 
should come to a decision on the situation no later than this 
week. 

</TEXT>

