<F P=100> Ecuador </F>
<H3> <TI>   Measures Adopted To Ensure Free Market System </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Measures Adopted To Ensure Free Market System </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0504045294 Madrid EFE in Spanish 2107 GMT 4 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA0504045294 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Quito, 4 Apr (EFE) -- It was reported here today 
that the Ecuadoran Government has implemented measures to ensure 
and encourage a free market system and to increase production in 
the country's different industrial sectors. According to the new 
rules, investments in Ecuador's private sector will not require 
a patent, license, registration, permit, or certificate. 
Meanwhile, numerous decrees, laws, and administrative rules 
that had placed restrictions or limitations on industry and free 
trade were repealed. 
  The price of all local or imported goods, products, and 
services will be subject only to the free market laws without 
state controls, which means their prices will be established by 
the law of supply and demand, based on their quality and price. 
The new rules state that all products, goods, and livestock will 
be allowed free movement, transportation, and transit across the 
country without having to obtain a license or administrative 
authorization. Also, from now on, all Ecuadoran goods and 
products are exportable, with a few exceptions subject to 
quotas, restrictions, or limitations foreseen in the Law for 
Expediting Exports and Over Water Routes. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-9916 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drlat065_r_94001" </HT>


