<H3> <TI>   Miner Reportedly Shot by Venezuelan Patrol </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Miner Reportedly Shot by Venezuelan Patrol </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY0404125494 Brasilia Radio Nacional da Amazonia Network in 
Portuguese 1000 GMT 4 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY0404125494 </F>
<F P=104>  Brasilia Radio Nacional da Amazonia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Venezuelan National Guard killed a Brazilian 
miner in the village of Parima, in the country's Amazon region. 
  According to official reports, the Brazilian miner -- who 
was 
known as Franco -- shot at a Venezuelan patrol when the patrol 
found an illegal camp in Parima, which served as a base for gold 
and diamond mining. 
  Brazilians Antonio Edilmar Ribeiro and Cicero Eduardo Britto 
were arrested and are being held in Puerto Ayacucho, the capital 
of the Amazon province. 

</TEXT>

