<HT>    "drlat065_k_94003" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-LAT-94-065 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  4 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> SOUTH AMERICA </F>
<F P=101> Argentina </F>
<H3> <TI>   Menem on Conversation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Menem on Conversation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY0404173694 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 
1518 GMT 4 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY0404173694 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Buenos Aires, 4 Apr (NA) -- President Carlos Menem 
today denied that his chat with Cuban chief of state Fidel 
Castro was reconciliatory, and he indicated that he had called 
Castro to recommend a nephew who had traveled to Havana because 
of health problems. 
  The Argentine president indicated that when he called his 
Cuban colleague, "Castro was about to make a toast with some 
Menem wine" that he himself had sent Castro. 
  Menem also indicated that he had taken advantage of the 
contact "to again thank him for the attention he gave a dear 
friend, (Cesar) Chacho Jaroslavsky, and to recommend a nephew 
who also had traveled to Cuba due to health reasons." 
  In remarks to Radio 990, Menem emphasized: "This was all we 
chatted about," and he said: "Our disagreements within the 
sphere of democracy and freedom will again be made known during 
the Cartagena de Indias summit above and beyond these aspects." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

