<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ricardo Alarcon Chairs Granma Deputies Meeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ricardo Alarcon Chairs Granma Deputies Meeting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL0504234694 Havana Radio Progreso Network in Spanish 1100 
GMT 5 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0504234694 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Progreso Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] According to the newspaper GRANMA, deputies have 
begun their analysis in preparation for the next session of the 
National Assembly of the People's Government [ANPP]. In Granma, 
ANPP President Ricardo Alarcon chaired the country's first 
meeting with deputies to analyze the results of Parliaments in 
the Workplaces and to note some of the ideas that could be used 
in preparation for the ANPP special session scheduled for 1 May. 
  Preliminary reports submitted by Deputy Ernesto Suarez, who 
is also an ANPP secretary, state that 3 million workers 
participated in the parliaments, by which the workers 
demonstrated their patriotism, honor, and willingness to do 
whatever might be necessary to save the Revolution. For that 
meeting, the ANPP president and seven permanent ANPP working 
committees visited Granma for the rendering of the province's 
accounts in preparation for the next special period of sessions 
of our parliament. 
  Rafael Dominguez Fernandez, president of the provincial 
government, released a report on the socioeconomic 
characteristics of Granma, its work objectives, and a rendering 
of its accounts. Also present were Deputy Jaime Crombet, who is 
a member of the Cuban Communist Party [PCC] Central Committee 
and vice president of the ANPP; and Alfredo Enriquez Pina, PCC 
first secretary. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

