<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   CTC Funds Earmarked for Pioneers Organization </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    CTC Funds Earmarked for Pioneers Organization </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL0604003894 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1700 
GMT 5 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0604003894 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On 5 April, the Cuban Workers Federation [CTC] 
announced that beginning this year, it will financially sponsor 
the Jose Marti Pioneers organization. Pedro Ross, Politburo 
member and secretary general of the CTC, made the announcement 
on 4 April in Camaguey following a ceremony marking the 
completion of the Jiguey Cayo-Romano Cayo Cruz causeway. Ross 
added that the decision was made on the basis of union dues 
contributed by the workers and which is their gift to the 
youngest organization in Cuba on its 33d anniversary, adding 
that 8 million pesos are already earmarked for that goal this 
year, thanks to expenditure reductions by the CTC. Ross pointed 
out that over the past three years, CTC expenditures have been 
less than 30 million pesos, and that in 1993 they were 28 
million as the result of reductions in personnel rosters and 
other expenditures. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

