<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Central Committee Member Dies of `Painful Illness' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Central Committee Member Dies of `Painful Illness' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL0504160094 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 0900 
GMT 5 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0504160094 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Comrade Eugenio Cuevas Ibanez, who had an 
outstanding record as a student leader and member of the Union 
of Young Communists [UJC] and the Communist Party of Cuba [PCC], 
has died at the age of 45, victim to a painful illness. Among 
the many positions he held, Cuevas was the first UJC secretary 
in Santiago de Cuba, a professional member of the Santiago de 
Cuba provincial PCC bureau, and first secretary of the PCC 
municipal committee in Palma Soriano. In 1992, he was elected 
first secretary of the Guantanamo provincial committee, a 
position he held as long as his health condition permitted. 
  At the time of his death, Cuevas was a member of the Central 
Committee of the PCC and a deputy of the National Assembly of 
the People's Government. His body can be viewed at the Bartolome 
Funeral Home in Santiago de Cuba. He will be buried today, 5 
April, at the Santa Efigenia Cemetery at 1400 GMT. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

