<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<H3> <TI>   PRI Secretary General Sworn In; Zedillo Manager Named </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PRI Secretary General Sworn In; Zedillo Manager Named </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0504152394 Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1424 GMT 5 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0504152394 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1424 GMT 5 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=105> Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Raul Sanchez Carrillo from the "Early Morning" </F>
newscast] 
  [Text] Now, we are at the Political Council of the National 
Executive Committee of the Institutional Revolutionary Party 
[PRI]. Ignacio Pichardo Pagaza was sworn in as secretary general 
of the PRI National Executive Committee a few minutes ago. 
Ignacio Pichardo Pagaza, who was former governor of Mexico 
State, will replace Jose Luis La Madrid Sauza, who resigned 
yesterday to accept the post of campaign coordinator for PRI 
presidential candidate Ernesto Zedillo Ponce de Leon. 
  Here at the Political Council, headed by Fernando Ortiz 
Arana 
as president of the National Executive Committee of the PRI, the 
election of Ignacio Pichardo Pagaza was unanimous. 
Representatives of the three groups that make up the party 
brought him to this room where the event is being held. 
  Currently, an agreement is being read which states that on 
orders from the candidate, Zedillo Ponce de Leon, himself, the 
mourning for the death of Luis Donaldo Colosio, who was cowardly 
assassinated, will be perpetuated within the party. His 
political ideology will be respected and fulfilled so as to 
strengthen the new presidential candidate. 

</TEXT>

