<F P=100> Nicaragua </F>
<H3> <TI>   Lawsuits Against EU on Banana Issues Withdrawn </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Lawsuits Against EU on Banana Issues Withdrawn </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0404163394 Managua Radio Nicaragua Network in Spanish 1200 
GMT 4 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0404163394 </F>
<F P=104>  Managua Radio Nicaragua Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "This Morning" newscast] </F>
  [Text] After signing an important agreement in Brussels the 
week of 28 March, Nicaragua withdrew its banana suits against 
the EU regarding the purchasing quotas and tariffs imposed by 
the EU on banana imports from Latin America. The agreement will 
benefit Nicaraguan banana exports. 
  According to reports from Belgium, Nicaragua, Costa Rica, 
Honduras, and Panama agreed not to begin any disputes within the 
framework of GATT against the 12 European banana buyers until 31 
December 2002. The agreement contemplates an increase in the 
banana purchasing quotas from 2 million tons a year to 2.2 
million tons for 1995. 

</TEXT>

