<F P=100> Panama </F>
<H3> <TI>   Business License Fees Raise $30 Million </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Business License Fees Raise $30 Million </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0504143194 </F>
<F P=103> PA0504143194 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
BFN 

    [Editorial report] Panama City LA PRENSA in Spanish on 3 
April p 11A reports that Delia de Castro, general director of 
domestic commerce of the Commerce and Industry Ministry, has 
announced that new business licenses contributed $30 million to 
the government's revenue during 1993. Each new corporation must 
pay 1 percent of its initial capital investment in taxes, she 
has said, and 7,506 new licenses were issued last year. Of 
these, 5,680 were for retail businesses, 647 for wholesale 
dealerships, and 476 for industrial enterprises. 

</TEXT>

