<F P=100> Peru </F>
<H3> <TI>   Obligations To Be `Gradually' Resumed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Obligations To Be `Gradually' Resumed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY0604013994 Lima Radio Programas del Peru Network in 
Spanish 1800 GMT 5 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY0604013994 </F>
<F P=104>  Lima Radio Programas del Peru Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Today, Industry Minister Liliana Canale said Peru 
will gradually resume its obligations with the Andean Pact. She 
added that Peru has not returned to the subregional group, which 
is also made up of Venezuela, Bolivia, Colombia, and Ecuador, 
because Peru never left that organization. 
  She indicated that Peru is only resuming its obligations 
with 
the Andean Pact based on certain conditions. Among these, she 
mentioned the fulfillment of the proposal made by Peru in the 
meeting being held in Caracas. Our country requested the 
elimination of any type of export subsidies as well as of the 
distortions in external tariffs. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

