<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Economic Developments </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Roundup of Economic Developments </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0504144994 </F>
<F P=103> PA0504144994 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
BFN 

    [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on Venezuelan economic developments monitored through 5 
April. 
  Venezuelan inflation reached 2.8 percent during March, 
according to a report issued by the Venezuelan Central Bank. The 
source has said the main contributor was household goods, 
followed by food, liquor, and tobacco. In the first three months 
of 1994, accumulated inflation was 9.3 percent, a slightly 
higher figure that that registered for the same period last 
year. (Hamburg DPA in Spanish 1442 GMT 2 April 94) 
  Venezuelan oil officials have said oil production levels 
will 
remain unchanged. Following two days of discussions in Geneva, 
Erwin Arrieta, mines and energy minister, announced OPEC expects 
to counter falling prices. He also announced that Venezuela has 
nominated Alirio Parra as a candidate for secretary general and 
that the election will be held at the next OPEC conference. 
(Caracas EL NACIONAL in Spanish 27 March 94 p-E2) 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

