<H3> <TI>   Argentine Official To Sign Drug Protocol </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Argentine Official To Sign Drug Protocol </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0504043894 Havana PRENSA LATINA in Spanish 1841 GMT 4 Apr 
94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> PA0504043894 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana PRENSA LATINA </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Havana, 4 Apr (PL) -- Today, official sources 
reported Argentine Secretary of State Alberto Lestelle is in 
Cuba to sign an agreement on drug addiction and drug trafficking. 
  The National Information Agency reports that Lestelle said 
the Cuban and Argentine Governments agreed to sign a formal 
mutual assistance protocol in which both parties will be jointly 
responsible in combating this problem, which transcends their 
national borders. 
  The Argentine leader said that, after months of working 
together with the Cuban Justice Ministry, Argentina has 
identified points of mutual interest in which they can cooperate. 
  He added that Argentina has been implementing a mutual 
assistance program on the American continent and many 
governments have requested assistance to train specialized 
personnel. 
  He noted that this has been done in Costa Rica, Guatemala, 
and the Dominican Republic, and he announced this will soon be 
established in Honduras and Nicaragua. 

</TEXT>

