<H3> <TI>   Haitian Foreign Minister To Address SELA </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Haitian Foreign Minister To Address SELA </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0604220594 Paris AFP in Spanish 1900 GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA0604220594 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Caracas, 6 Apr (AFP) -- Claudette Werleigh, foreign 
minister of Haiti's constitutional government, will explain her 
country's political situation to representatives of 
international organizations and ambassadors to the Latin 
American Economic System (SELA), it was reported Wednesday. 
SELA headquarters are in Caracas. 
  SELA spokesmen said that representatives of the World Bank, 
the Inter-American Development Bank, the OAS, UNESCO, the 
International Organization for Immigrants, and the UNHCR will 
attend the meeting. 
  The ambassadors from Barbados, Grenada, Guyana, Suriname, 
Trinidad and Tobago, and Jamaica will also attend. 
  During the last SELA Latin American Council held in Caracas 
in October 1993, representatives of the 27 member states signed 
a solidarity declaration with the Haitian people expressing 
their "deep concern for the lack of constitutional order in that 
country." 
  The Council recommended that the SELA Permanent Secretariat 
"follow up on the situation in Haiti and remain alert so upon 
restoration of constitutional rule," a cooperation program can 
be immediately implemented. 

</TEXT>

