<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Paraguay's Ramirez Cited on `Unofficial' Robaina Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Paraguay's Ramirez Cited on `Unofficial' Robaina Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL0604142394 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 0900 
GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0604142394 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Uruguayan Foreign Minister Sergio Abreu said, 
shortly after meeting with his Cuban counterpart Roberto Robaina 
in Montevideo, that there are no difficulties in the relations 
between Cuba and Uruguay. [passage omitted] 
  Meanwhile, Paraguayan Foreign Minister Luis Maria Ramirez 
has 
said that Robaina will make an unofficial visit to Paraguay in 
the next few days. Ramirez added that Paraguayan President Juan 
Carlos Wasmosy will not be able to receive Robaina because he is 
traveling in Europe, and that he himself, Ramirez, will not be 
able to receive Robaina either, because he is leaving today for 
Morocco to participate in the signing of the agreement on the 
Uruguay Round of the GATT. 
  Diplomatic relations between Havana and Asuncion do not 
exist 
at the present time, but Robaina's presence in Paraguay is 
considered the first reflection of the intention toward 
rapprochement between Paraguay and Cuba. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

