<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Guerrillero-94 Exercise Begins in Guantanamo </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Guerrillero-94 Exercise Begins in Guantanamo </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL0604144194 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 1946 GMT 
5 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0604144194 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The executive phase of the Guerrillero-94 exercise 
began on 5 April in Guantanamo. The purpose of the exercise is 
to evaluate the efficiency of the Unified Vigilance and 
Protection System. The exercise will enhance the control and 
operation structures of the system at each level and increase 
cohesion at workplaces, organizations, and enterprises to 
preserve economic resources. 
  The Executive Secretariat of the Committees for the Defense 
of the Revolution in Holguin has called upon its members to 
honor their commitment to the people's surveillance program. 
The measures include performing the entire watch, staying 
alert, and not letting other tasks distract from the 
effectiveness of the watch, as well as fulfilling the watch 
during power outages. 

</TEXT>

