<H3> <TI>   President Salinas Welcomes Nicaragua's Chamorro </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Salinas Welcomes Nicaragua's Chamorro </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0604180394 Mexico City XEW Television Network in Spanish 
0430 GMT 5 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0604180394 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City XEW Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "24 Hours" newscast] </F>
  [Text] President Carlos Salinas de Gortari has welcomed 
Nicaraguan President Violeta Chamorro to Mexico on a three-day 
official visit. President Salinas met with President Chamorro 
at the National Presidential Palace. After listening to both 
countries' national anthems which were played in the palace 
gardens, President Salinas said during President Chamorro's 
visit the two leaders will expand several current agreements to 
provide greater prosperity and justice for both Mexicans and 
Nicaraguans. 
  [Begin Salinas recording] During these times of world 
change, we must join efforts, increase trade, and complement 
each other's economies. We will move forward by taking specific 
action. The challenge is to take advantage of our capabilities, 
our enthusiasm, and the common causes that bond us. [end 
recording] 

</TEXT>

