<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<H3> <TI>   PRI Member Resigns Over Party Differences </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PRI Member Resigns Over Party Differences </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0604122494 Mexico City Radio ACIR Network in Spanish 0000 
GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0604122494 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Radio ACIR Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "ACIR Radio News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Demetrio Sodi de la Tijera, member of the 
Legislative Assembly for the Federal District, explains that his 
departure from the PRI [Institutional Revolutionary Party] is 
because he does not agree with the way his party's new 
presidential candidate was elected. 
  [Begin Sodi de la Tijera recording] I am leaving because of 
the way the new candidate was chosen. As far as the candidate 
is concerned, I have no rapport with nor do I believe he has the 
experience to become president of the republic. It would not be 
compatible to belong to a party and not agree with the candidate 
or the aspiring candidates. This is why I decided to resign. 
[end recording] 
  It is expected that tomorrow, Thursday [as heard], he will 
make his departure from the PRI official. Meanwhile, Rene 
Bejaranom, Democratic Revolutionary Party leader in Mexico City, 
said his party would be willing to offer a Senate candidacy for 
the Federal District to Demetrio Sodi de la Tijera. 

</TEXT>

