<F P=100> Guatemala </F>
<H3> <TI>   Deputy Chinchilla Shot, in Critical Condition </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Deputy Chinchilla Shot, in Critical Condition </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0704010894 Panama City ACAN in Spanish 2349 GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA0704010894 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City ACAN </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Guatemala City, 6 Apr (ACAN-EFE) -- According to 
local media sources, Revolutionary Party Deputy Obdulio 
Chinchilla was wounded today when unidentified persons shot him 
as he was leaving a hotel in the capital. This is the second 
attack against Chinchilla in less than a year. 
  The legislator, finance committee chairman, and chairman of 
the commission studying reforms to the electoral and political 
parties laws, was shot several times, but there is still no 
information on the seriousness of his injuries, Radio Sonora 
reported. 
  The motives of Chinchilla's attackers are still unknown. 
Chinchilla was the target of another attack months ago which 
caused him to lose one eye. This attack has occurred five days 
after Constitutionality Court President Epaminondas Gonzalez was 
assassinated in front of his house. No one has claimed 
responsibility for that attack. 
  [Paris AFP in Spanish at 2342 GMT transmits a report which 
states that "Chinchilla was transferred in critical condition to 
a private hospital." The report adds that "one suspect has 
apparently been arrested."] 

</TEXT>

