<F P=100> SOUTH AMERICA </F>
<F P=101> Argentina </F>
<H3> <TI>   Argentine-U.S. Navies Begin Joint Exercises </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Argentine-U.S. Navies Begin Joint Exercises </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY0604140594 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 
2317 GMT 5 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY0604140594 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Buenos Aires, 5 Apr (NA) -- The Argentine Navy 
reported today that it will participate in a joint exercise with 
the U.S. Navy off the Atlantic coast near the Norfolk Naval 
Base, Virginia, between 6 and 22 April. 
  The Navy said the invitation to participate in the exercise 
was made within the framework of existing professional relations 
between the two countries. 
  The Argentine task force will be commanded by Navy Captain 
Rafael Fuentes y Arballo and will include the destroyer ARA 
[Argentine Republic Navy] La Argentina. The United States task 
force will include the flagship USS Mount Wintney, the nuclear 
aircraft carrier George Washington, and nuclear cruisers and 
submarines. 
  The operation will consist of isolating an aircraft carrier 
battle group and an amphibious group. Activities will be headed 
by the commander of the U.S. Second Fleet. 
  The Argentine Navy units, some of the newest in the country, 
will have an opportunity to repeat the interaction experiences 
in face of foreign forces. 
  At the end of the operation, in answer to Canadian Navy 
offer, the Argentine destroyer will make an official visit to 
Halifax port to participate in a brief training exercise with 
Canadian Navy units. 

</TEXT>

