<H3> <TI>   Arrests, `Chaotic Situation' Continue in Jujuy </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Arrests, `Chaotic Situation' Continue in Jujuy </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY0604193694 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 
2347 GMT 5 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY0604193694 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] San Salvador de Jujuy, 5 Apr (NA) -- This 
provincial capital today again experienced a chaotic situation 
after new clashes between the police and public servants were 
reported. The clashes left a toll of at least a dozen injured 
people and about 20 detainees, including Carlos "Dog" Santillan, 
the Trade Union of Municipal Employees and Workers [Sindicato de 
Empleados y Obreros Municipales] (SEOM) leader. 
  Trade union leader Santillan, who is among those conducting 
the mobilizations being carried out by public servants to 
receive salary hikes, was arrested at noon today, and his 
whereabouts remained unknown for several hours. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

