<F P=100> Chile </F>
<H3> <TI>   Pinochet Appoints Officers to Army High Command </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Pinochet Appoints Officers to Army High Command </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY0704141994 Santiago LA TERCERA DE LA HORA in Spanish 24 
Mar 94 p 7 </F>

<F P=103> PY0704141994 </F>
<F P=104>  Santiago LA TERCERA DE LA HORA </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Army Commander General Augusto Pinochet 
yesterday completed the Army high command with the appointment 
of General Jaime Concha, current Advisory Committee chief, as 
Army inspector general. Gen. Concha replaces General Jorge 
Ballerino, who resigned on 31 January. [passage omitted] 
  Thus, the Army command reads: 
  Army Commander in Chief: General Augusto Pinochet. Deputy 
Commander in Chief: Lieutenant Colonel Jorge Lucar. Major 
General Guillermo Garin remains in his position as commander of 
the 1st Army Corps; Major General Richard Quass is the Army 
chief of staff; Major General Ramon Castro Ivanovic is the 
personnel director; Major General Eterio Pavez is the commander 
of the Southern Military Region; Major General Jaime Concha is 
the Army inspector general; Major General Guido Riquelme is the 
commander general of the Metropolitan Region Army Garrison; 
Major General Ricardo Gaete Villasenor is the deputy Army chief 
of staff; Major General Hernan Abad Cid is the commander of the 
Engineers Command; Brigadier General Hernan Ramirez Rurange is 
the commander of the 2d Army Division; Brigadier General Javier 
Salazar is the director of the Strategic and Political Studies 
Academy (Anepe); and Brigadier General Carlos Krumm is the 
director of the Army Logistic Division. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

