<F P=100> Chile </F>
<H3> <TI>   Aeronautical Enterprise To Maintain Spanish Planes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Aeronautical Enterprise To Maintain Spanish Planes </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY0604233894 Santiago EL MERCURIO in Spanish 23 Mar 94 p C5 </F>
<F P=103> PY0604233894 </F>
<F P=104>  Santiago EL MERCURIO </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] The National Aeronautical Enterprise, Enaer, 
will become a center for repairing the Casa-212 and 235 
transportation airplanes, which are used mostly in the Latin 
American countries. 
  The information was provided by engineer Raul Herranz, a 
specialist in nuclear energy and president of Construcciones 
Aeronauticas S.A., CASA, of Spain, which manufactures the 
airplanes used in about 10 countries on the continent. [passage 
omitted] 
  Herranz pointed out the high level of efficiency of Enaer, 
which co-produces the advanced C-101 training airplane -- known 
as the T- 36 Halcon -- in Chile, as well as the ability of its 
engineers and support personnel who work in the arsenals. 
  He added: "This is why the Chilean company was chosen to 
represent us in Latin America for the maintenance or repair of 
all CASA products. We already have that commitment, which is 
unique because no authorization of this type to an industry has 
been given in any other part of the world." 
  He said the exchange of aeronautics technology between Spain 
and Chile has been fluid, and this transfer of technology will 
be strengthened soon with the signing of a new contract. He 
added: "We are open to any type of cooperation with Enaer." 

</TEXT>

