<H3> <TI>   Armed Forces Chiefs Express Loyalty to Fujimori </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Armed Forces Chiefs Express Loyalty to Fujimori </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY0704031794 Lima Global de Television Network in Spanish 
0100 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY0704031794 </F>
<F P=104>  Lima Global de Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Armed Forces Joint Command issued an official 
communique stating its loyalty to the president of the Republic 
on the occasion of the second anniversary of the institutional 
change that took place on 5 April. 
  It says that the support given to the president's decision 
was appropriate because it was based on the true situation of a 
country that is now on the way to achieving the desired national 
pacification after a period of chaos. 
  The communique signed by the head of the Armed Forces Joint 
Command, the military commanders, and the National Police 
general director says they will continue to work to consolidate 
this process that is the basis and guarantee for a lasting and 
stable democracy. 

